WEBVTT

00:01.793 --> 00:03.754
- All right, who's ready
to have a good time, huh?

00:03.837 --> 00:05.923
That's right. That's what I like to hear.

00:06.006 --> 00:08.175
Uh, show of hands,
how many people have, uh,

00:08.258 --> 00:10.219
been to a taping of a TV show before?

00:10.302 --> 00:11.845
- Thank you. Okay.

00:11.929 --> 00:14.806
Just remember: "The movie's hilarious.

00:14.890 --> 00:16.225
Everyone buy tickets."

00:16.308 --> 00:17.643
- Let me ask you a question.
- Yeah.

00:17.726 --> 00:19.728
- Do you think I'm good in the movie?

00:19.811 --> 00:21.897
- Come on, Kev. I'm your agent.
Of course I think you're good

00:21.980 --> 00:23.941
in the movie. You know who else
thinks you're good in the movie?

00:24.024 --> 00:25.859
The studio.

00:25.943 --> 00:27.736
Now go knock 'em dead.
Big smiles, big laughs.

00:27.819 --> 00:30.322
America's funny man.

00:30.405 --> 00:32.491
- And, uh, we're gonna have a great time,
all right?

00:32.574 --> 00:33.909
- "America's funny man."

00:37.162 --> 00:39.831
- Oh, now, Kev, people are just raving

00:39.915 --> 00:42.876
about this new movie of yours.
- Oh, my God, they're raving.

00:42.960 --> 00:44.461
- You are working with

00:44.545 --> 00:46.463
Dwayne "The Rock" Johnson,

00:46.547 --> 00:48.257
playing his comedy sidekick again.

00:48.340 --> 00:49.883
What is this, the sixth time now?

00:49.967 --> 00:51.051
- Number six.

00:51.134 --> 00:52.803
- How do you keep it so fresh?

00:52.886 --> 00:55.097
- I mean, look, Dwayne and I are, um...

00:55.180 --> 00:56.515
You know, we're friends.

00:56.598 --> 00:57.641
- #Jealous.
- Lucky.

00:59.142 --> 01:01.937
- He's lucky, too. He's lucky, too.

01:02.020 --> 01:03.730
But I mean, look, when you are friends,

01:03.814 --> 01:05.148
you feed off of each other.

01:05.232 --> 01:07.734
That energy, of course, transfers,
but, uh,

01:07.818 --> 01:09.820
I don't know, I would like to think of
my, my characters

01:09.903 --> 01:11.822
as, as heroes, as well.

01:13.991 --> 01:15.909
I-I don't know what the...

01:15.993 --> 01:17.744
I don't know why they laugh.

01:17.828 --> 01:19.371
I'm very serious.

01:19.454 --> 01:20.998
You know, I've-I've actually...
I've been...

01:21.081 --> 01:23.292
I've been trying to become
a leading man, you know?

01:23.375 --> 01:25.127
Do more of an action star thing.

01:25.210 --> 01:27.212
But I've been...
I've been somewhat typecast.

01:27.296 --> 01:29.131
For some reason,
people only see me as the funny guy.

01:29.214 --> 01:31.049
- You make me laugh.
- Yeah.
- No. Thank you. Glad...

01:31.133 --> 01:32.676
Glad, you know, appreciate it.
- I'm not an easy audience.

01:34.261 --> 01:36.180
- Yeah, you know, but it's just...
It's... I can do more

01:36.263 --> 01:40.267
than show up and do the funny
or do the dance. I'm...

01:40.350 --> 01:42.102
- Would you, though?
- Would you do that dance?

01:42.186 --> 01:43.228
- Come on.
- Come on.

01:43.312 --> 01:44.605
Who wants to see Kevin dance?

01:44.688 --> 01:46.190
Huh?

01:46.273 --> 01:47.816
- We'll get the Macarena going. Anybody?

01:47.900 --> 01:49.443
- We would love that.
- No.

01:49.526 --> 01:51.278
No.

01:51.361 --> 01:53.030
I'm not... I'm not gonna dance.

01:53.113 --> 01:55.199
- Next time. Next time, then, for sure.

01:55.282 --> 01:56.783
- Oh, dear.
- Uh, but getting back to the movie,

01:56.867 --> 01:58.660
t-tell-tell us
just how great this movie is.

01:58.744 --> 02:00.078
- The, uh, the movie's garbage.

02:00.162 --> 02:01.496
- Sorry.

02:01.580 --> 02:03.498
- Yeah. The movie's garbage.

02:03.582 --> 02:05.125
Take the movie, ball it up,

02:05.209 --> 02:06.543
throw it in the trash can.

02:06.627 --> 02:08.128
How many times do you need to see me

02:08.212 --> 02:10.881
in a car with Dwayne "The Rock" Johnson,

02:10.964 --> 02:13.383
and I'm the comedy sidekick,
and he's saving lives,

02:13.467 --> 02:16.178
and I got a catchphrase: "Oh, hell no!"?

02:16.261 --> 02:17.429
- We love it when you say that.

02:17.513 --> 02:19.056
- Oh, yeah. Can you do it again?
- Yeah.

02:19.139 --> 02:20.849
- Here's my question:
why can't I be an action star?

02:20.933 --> 02:22.893
- I read something online

02:22.976 --> 02:24.686
a-about, uh, you being

02:24.770 --> 02:26.939
afraid of woodland creatures.
- Oh, yes.

02:27.022 --> 02:28.565
- About me what?
- A beaver?

02:28.649 --> 02:30.526
It was a s-squirrel. A squirrel.
- A squirrel. It was a squirrel.

02:30.609 --> 02:31.527
-Yes, that you have a fear of squirrels.

02:31.610 --> 02:32.736
- And who's afraid of a squirrel?

02:32.819 --> 02:34.071
- I'm not fucking afraid of a squirrel!

02:34.154 --> 02:35.948
- Okay.
- I'm not afraid of shit.

02:36.031 --> 02:37.241
- Okay, you've said it.
You've made your point there.

02:37.324 --> 02:39.243
- I'm not afraid of shit.
- Yeah.

02:39.326 --> 02:40.577
- And I'm more than just the guy
that does comedy.

02:40.661 --> 02:41.995
I'm a fucking action star, all right?

02:42.079 --> 02:43.622
So why don't you start taking me
a little serious?

02:43.705 --> 02:46.083
Tell me what I am and what I'm not.

02:46.166 --> 02:49.044
If I didn't have what the fuck it takes,
would I show this?

02:49.127 --> 02:52.214
Or that?

02:52.297 --> 02:53.632
Back up!
- Yup.

02:53.715 --> 02:55.217
- Whoa, Kev, Kev, Kev. Kev, hey.

02:55.300 --> 02:57.177
You got to go back out there,
say it was a joke.

02:57.261 --> 02:59.221
- Talking about "it was a joke"?
You don't get it, man.

02:59.304 --> 03:01.014
All right?
I'm trying to be taken seriously.

03:01.098 --> 03:03.350
My whole life,
I've dreamed of becoming an action hero.

03:03.433 --> 03:05.102
- Well, you know,
maybe instead of dreaming,

03:05.185 --> 03:06.854
you should just stay in your own lane.

03:06.937 --> 03:08.105
- What the fuck did you just say?

03:08.188 --> 03:09.648
- What are you doing?

03:15.279 --> 03:17.573
- It was a bit. We were doing a bit.

03:21.201 --> 03:23.078
- I'm not afraid of [bleep].
- Okay, you've said it.

03:23.161 --> 03:24.746
You've made your point there.
- I'm not afraid of [bleep].

03:24.830 --> 03:26.164
- Yeah.
- And I'm more than just

03:26.248 --> 03:27.666
the guy that does comedy.

03:27.749 --> 03:29.084
I'm a [bleep] action star, all right?

03:29.168 --> 03:30.335
So why don't you start [bleep]?

03:30.419 --> 03:32.462
- That was our star Kevin Hart,

03:32.546 --> 03:36.675
and apparently he's...
going through something.

03:36.758 --> 03:38.886
- To say the least.
You don't see Tom Cruise...

03:44.349 --> 03:46.101
- I already know what you're gonna say.

03:46.185 --> 03:48.020
